2026-04-15 | Shortest Distance to Target in Circular Array

	Question
Return minimum steps required, or -1 if target not found.

	Approach
1.	Traverse all indices:
		if words[i] == target  

2.	For each such index:
		calculate distance in both directions:
			rightDist = abs(i - startIndex)  
			leftDist = n - rightDist  

3.	Take minimum:
		min(rightDist, leftDist)

4.	Track global minimum  

5.	If target never found → return -1  

	Time Complexity
	O(n)

	Space Complexity
	O(1)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    int closestTarget(vector<string>& words, string target, int startIndex) {

        int n = words.size();
        int ans = INT_MAX;

        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){

            if(words[i] == target){

                int diff = abs(i - startIndex);
                int dist = min(diff, n - diff);

                ans = min(ans, dist);
            }
        }

        return ans == INT_MAX ? -1 : ans;
    }
};

	Key Insight
In a circular array:
		distance = min(|i - start|, n - |i - start|)  

So we simply check all target positions and pick the minimum circular distance.
